CatDescriptText: Josephine Wilson, recent high school graduate, 35 Carmel Way, was part of the "Pittsburghers Speak Up" column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, January 24, 1959, pg. A1 with question: "Do you think that the increasing demand for father and mother to work, thus taking both parents out of the home for the better part of the day, affects their children as regards discipline, ambition, and social compatibility in general?" answer reads: "In some ways, I think that it does.  Although, it is a necessity for both parents to be working in some families, a babysitter never can take the place of a mother in disciplining the children."
